      • read

        public boolean read(Trial trial,
                    java.io.InputStream is)
             throws TrialException
        Reads the specified XML file and returns true if the import was successful. If the import was successful, then the lists for the imported objects will be valid after this method returns.
        Specified by:
        read in interface TrialDataImporter
        Parameters:
        trial - the trial that the data is being imported into. Cannot be null.
        is - the ImportStream to read the data from.
        Returns:
        true if the import was successful; otherwise false is returned.
        Throws:
        TrialException - indicates an error occurred while operating on the file.
